	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Seriously.<br><br>I made a lot of friends when I started EQ, and they are still good friends.&nbsp;&nbsp;But for some reason, I have levelled a LOT faster then they have.  I am level 48, and the highest of my friends is at 31.<br><br>I joined a newbie/lowbie guild when I was about level 7 or so, and at the time the highest level member was about 18.  Now I am the highest level player in my guild by about 20 levels.<br><br>So . . . I have nobody to group with among my friends or guildies =(<br><br>I enjoy helping my friends when they ask.  I have thought about looking for a higher level guild, but I am loyal to my guildies and the leader, and I know eventually they will catch up.<br><br>But in the meantime, I am spending almost all of my time soloing, except when I am helping people.  That isn't too bad, but I enjoy grouping and meeting people and learning tactics.<br><br>Problem is, many of the higher level zones are BYOG, and pick-up groups can be dangerous, if you know what I mean.<br><br>I would appreciate any suggestions regarding my dilemma.<br><br>Thanks!<br>&nbsp;<br>Duggall<br>Heirophant of Morell Thule<br>Reviction</td></tr>
