	   <tr><td colspan=2>K, Duggall I'll try and answer your post, rather than tangenting:) The way I see it you have 4 choices:<br>1. Solo Vox till your back to the approximate lvl of your friends(I DO NOT recommend this solution but just had to throw it out there)<br>2. Find the hunting spots that you like, and look for pick up groups there. Yes it can be dangerous but at least its someplace you feel a little comfortable with. And you never know who you'll get in a group, but after a bit you will find others whom you feel comfortable covering your back. Plus That tank who's butt you just pulled out of the fire because the cleric was oom just might remember you when he needs a good group member for those phat lewt raids:)<br>3. Solo. but all this will do is get you even farther from your friends/guildies levels<br>4. Start powerleveling your friends/guildies and make your own groups. Slow , sometimes painful, but then again can be fun:)<br><br>most of these have merit( I said most so dont harrass me about #1:) So take care try to have fun, and good luck:)<br><br><br>Kay<br>&nbsp;<br>Im just here for the beer</td></tr>
