	   <tr><td colspan=2>Besides using DDs like burn spells, I've also seen druids using AoE spells like mad in groups.&nbsp;&nbsp;This kind of irks me and my chanter friend who I tend to partner/group with often because this breaks mez no matter how it is used.  I myself am a druid and although I say that 95% of the "bad rep" given to druids is undeserved... I have seen that 5% of the druid population who don't know how to group effectivly.  Tips for new druids... Get into groups early even if you make more XP soloing.  It's fun and worthwhile.  I rarely play without a group and when I do, I definitly don't have as much fun.  When you do get into a group... as a general rule, never use DD and AoE spells.  Your mana is better spent on healing and DOT spells.  At the higher levels... post 20... don't try to melee.  You'll just end up dying more often than not if the warrior can't taunt.<br>&nbsp;<br>Rillen Tel'rhovanion<br>Druid of 40 seasons<br>Tal Kor ~ Fennin Ro</td></tr>
