<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98880478968642></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98880478968642><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98880478968642>RE: Levelled too fast!  48 Druid LFG on Morell Thule</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98880478968642#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17974><span id=Scholar>mpete</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>216 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 2nd 7:59 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.53]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>DOT in groups??&nbsp;&nbsp;/BOGGLE: confusion sets in.  Most posts I read people complain when druids do use DOTs in a group.  They complain the MOBS drop too fast for our DOT's to work in groups.  I tried one time to use DOT's in a group and not one but two group members quickly said not to do it.  They wanted me to use my dd and backup heal as we did have a good cleric.  As for solo not being fun I disagree.  I have a blast soloing.  Now like most things it does get boring if that's all you do.  Groups are fun too but also can get dull if that's all you do.  AoE's are not all bad!!  I do tend to avoid them when a chanter is present but they have there place in groups but you have to be careful.  The honest (dirty little secret) is most groups want druids to heal.  Even if a cleric is in the group your best purpose is to conserve mana for those nasty pulls that the cleric goes oom.  Also it's a good idea for the druid to have a lock on the clerics health.  When the cleric starts healing the MOBS get mad.  Then they proceed to beat the cleric down.  I am always prepared with my heal, snare, root, and dd's to get MOBS off the cleric.  The warriors may not be able to taunt fast enough to save your cleric every time.  Before anyone flames me saying druids are much more than healers in a group, STOP!!  I know we are more.  The fact is however we are usually not wanted or needed for much more.  I have learned to live with this and I am very liked in groups.  I do enjoy the rare ocassion when I can nuke, dot, crowd control, ect.  It spices up things a bit.  The bottom line is try to find out the groups wants and needs and fill them.  The beauty of being a druid is we are flexible if you learn your abilities well. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
